-Hey.
-You okay?

39:46.552 --> 39:49.294
-I'm drunk.
-Oh, okay. Well, you deserve to be.

39:49.471 --> 39:51.336
Have you seen Arlene?

39:51.515 --> 39:52.755
No, have--?

39:52.933 --> 39:54.264
Have you seen Bill?

39:58.021 --> 39:59.272
[MAN 1 SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

39:59.439 --> 40:00.770
There's a safe house...

40:00.941 --> 40:02.772
...just on the other Side of the bridge.

40:03.277 --> 40:05.142
That's good people.

40:05.320 --> 40:09.529
They'll give us food, Shelter for the night.

40:10.367 --> 40:11.573
Get our strength up...

40:13.036 --> 40:15.322
...so we can keep going north
come morning.

40:15.497 --> 40:16.577
[HORSE NEIGHS]

40:16.790 --> 40:18.246
Shh. Get down. Everybody down.

40:18.458 --> 40:21.586
MAN 2: Keep going!
MAN 3: All right, come on.

40:22.004 --> 40:23.619
[BABY CRYING]

40:23.797 --> 40:26.209
[SHUSHING]

40:26.383 --> 40:28.169
[CRYING CONTINUES]

40:42.024 --> 40:44.185
Okay, they're gone. We're safe.

40:44.610 --> 40:47.226
-You scared?
-Yeah, I suppose I am.

40:50.073 --> 40:52.735
All right, folks, it's gonna be all right.

40:52.909 --> 40:55.161
We gots to keep moving, though.

40:55.329 --> 40:57.365
MAN 4: Let's go.
-We've come thiS far and we almost--

40:57.539 --> 40:59.655
[GUNSHOT]

41:00.042 --> 41:01.578
[BABY CRYING]

41:01.960 --> 41:04.622
Well, well, look who we have here.

41:05.255 --> 41:09.168
You had no right to kill that man.
He was a good man.

41:09.343 --> 41:11.504
-You had no goddamn right.
-Oh, actually, I do.

41:11.720 --> 41:15.383
Now, if you would kindly
hand over that map.

41:16.391 --> 41:18.131
[BABY CONTINUES CRYING]

41:19.561 --> 41:21.301
Do it!

41:34.409 --> 41:36.570
Hey. Hey!

41:38.372 --> 41:41.159
-No!No!No!
-Get out of the way, Caroline!

41:41.375 --> 41:44.492
Please, Charles, I beg of you.
Please think of the children.

41:44.795 --> 41:45.830
[G RU NTS]

41:47.798 --> 41:49.288
[YELLS THEN GUNSHOT]

41:50.550 --> 41:55.169
You let that man serve as a warning
of what we do to any and all deserters...

41:55.389 --> 41:57.721
...no matter what their color.

41:58.475 --> 41:59.840
Hyah!

42:04.815 --> 42:06.806
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING INSIDE]

42:11.238 --> 42:14.480
Bill? I'm coming out.

42:14.700 --> 42:16.486
IS it safe?

42:16.660 --> 42:18.946
Yeah, it's safe, Sookie.

42:33.510 --> 42:35.717
You don't look quite right. Are you okay?

42:35.929 --> 42:38.921
-I'm fine. I'm just thinking is all.
-Well, then, stop.

42:39.141 --> 42:43.601
The whole point of this celebration is so that
we don't Sit around here with long faces.

42:45.522 --> 42:47.763
You haven't socialized at all tonight.

42:48.400 --> 42:50.937
I know everyone's pleased to see you here.

42:51.111 --> 42:53.853
No, they're pleased to see you, Sookie.

42:55.365 --> 42:56.775
You've done well.

42:57.868 --> 43:03.283
You've done more these last several days
than I've managed to achieve in decades.

43:10.046 --> 43:11.252
Mainstreaming.

43:15.010 --> 43:17.752
-I didn't do this.
-Yeah, you did.

43:23.059 --> 43:24.595
Well...

43:25.604 --> 43:27.265
...I've had a lovely evening.

43:27.481 --> 43:28.596
SOOKIE:
You can't leave yet.

43:28.774 --> 43:30.810
BILL:
No, I Should be on my way.

43:31.026 --> 43:33.438
But I had a wonderful time.

43:33.612 --> 43:39.403
But I must admit, this concept of
men and women being friends...

43:39.576 --> 43:42.067
...waS a little bit foreign in my day.

43:43.246 --> 43:46.534
-Bi||?
-Yeah?

43:47.834 --> 43:48.869
Thank you.

43:50.378 --> 43:51.413
For what?

43:52.464 --> 43:56.173
For seeing me the way
I can't see myself sometimes.

44:07.687 --> 44:09.348
Come on.

44:16.571 --> 44:18.277
Good night, Bill.

44:19.449 --> 44:20.950
Good night, Sookie.

44:28.375 --> 44:31.367
WOMAN: Look at her smiling like that,
how she lights up the room.

44:31.545 --> 44:33.410
LETTIE MAE:
Heard Willa was here.

44:33.588 --> 44:37.672
Can 't figure out what my Tara 's trying to tell me
unless I get me some of Willa '3 blood.

44:37.843 --> 44:39.834
Don ’t care ifl have to stab her to get it.

44:40.011 --> 44:41.876
Where's Willa?

44:42.055 --> 44:44.011
-Hey. Where's Willa?
-Who the fuck's Willa?

44:44.432 --> 44:47.094
-Dance with me.
-No. Willa?

44:47.310 --> 44:52.304
Sugar, I've had a little too much to drink,
so you're gonna just have to get to the point.

44:52.524 --> 44:56.392
Okay, Since Eric released me, I need a job,
so I was wondering if maybe...

44:56.611 --> 44:58.192
-...I could be a waitress--
-Lettie Mae, stop.

44:58.363 --> 45:00.649
-Aah!
-What the fuck?

45:00.866 --> 45:02.402
[GRUNTING]

45:03.869 --> 45:06.326
-Get back! Get the fuck back!
WILLA: I'm okay.

45:06.538 --> 45:08.449
-I'm okay.
SAM: She's okay.

45:08.665 --> 45:11.281
She's okay, y'all. Put your fangs away.

45:13.253 --> 45:14.868
LAFAYETTE:
What the hell's goings on here?

45:15.338 --> 45:17.294
Lettie Mae stabbed Willa.

45:17.465 --> 45:20.298
Of course she did. What the fuck, Auntie?

45:20.468 --> 45:23.801
Tara has been trying to contact me
from the other Side. She's stuck.

45:24.014 --> 45:27.598
And the only way I can find out what she needs
is with Willa's blood.

45:27.809 --> 45:32.018
-Come on, before you get killed. Come on.
-You're all looking at me like I'm crazy.

45:32.188 --> 45:35.271
Because I used to have a drinking problem,
people don't believe me.

45:35.442 --> 45:40.106
You stabbed somebody, Auntie.
That's why people think you crazy. Come on.

45:43.325 --> 45:46.112
You're all fucking crazy, if you ask me.

45:46.328 --> 45:48.193
What the fuck are we doing here?

45:48.413 --> 45:51.120
Huh? When just three days ago
a group of rabid vampires...

45:51.291 --> 45:55.455
...came and attacked the town and killed
a bunch of people and kidnapped us, right?

45:55.629 --> 45:59.372
Arlene, Jane, Holly and I, we were
fucking chained in a dungeon and we--

45:59.591 --> 46:01.673
Let's go to another room and talk about this.

46:01.843 --> 46:03.674
-Oh, no, no, no. No, Sam.
-Okay?

46:03.887 --> 46:07.425
No. I know you don't wanna hear this,
but it needs to be said. It's real.

46:07.641 --> 46:10.257
Damn it, people are dead,
people are traumatized...

46:10.435 --> 46:13.927
...and the reaction you all have to this
is to throw a party?

46:14.648 --> 46:16.889
You fucking kidding me?

46:17.067 --> 46:20.776
Now, I ain't for stabbing people,
but at least Lettie Mae gets it.

46:20.987 --> 46:24.320
Shit, I mean, you all are going on
like this Shit'S normal, and it's not.

46:24.532 --> 46:26.523
This shit doesn't happen in other towns.

46:29.120 --> 46:31.327
-Take me home. I wanna go home.
-Hey.

46:31.539 --> 46:33.700
-I wanna go home.
-Hey, hey. Here's your knife.

46:33.917 --> 46:35.123
Thanks.

46:36.670 --> 46:39.503
-Hey, I'm gonna make sure they get home safe.
-Thanks, Violet.

46:44.803 --> 46:45.963
I don't know.

46:46.429 --> 46:48.090
Maybe Lafayette is right.

46:48.306 --> 46:49.807
-What about?
-James and I.

46:50.016 --> 46:51.722
Maybe we don't belong together.

46:52.352 --> 46:54.638
You did meet in a prison camp, Jess.

46:54.813 --> 46:59.182
Careful, Jason. You know, people in
glass houses shouldn't throw stones.

47:02.529 --> 47:05.271
Yeah, Violet.

47:07.075 --> 47:09.942
She's pretty weird, ain't She?

47:10.120 --> 47:11.701
I mean, she's--

47:11.871 --> 47:16.410
She's ancient and sexy as hell,
but she's a little....

47:17.210 --> 47:18.666
-Off?
-Yeah.

47:18.962 --> 47:22.921
Ha, ha. She's way the fuck off sometimes.

47:24.009 --> 47:26.546
You think maybe that's why...?

47:27.887 --> 47:29.388
No, why what?

47:30.807 --> 47:33.423
We're supposed to be talking
about you, JeSS.

47:33.601 --> 47:37.185
Yeah, I don't really feel like thinking
about me anymore. Go on.

47:37.605 --> 47:40.312
-What?
-Well, okay, then.

47:40.483 --> 47:44.192
It was like earlier tonight,
when we were digging in...

47:44.362 --> 47:46.853
...trying to find Gran's ring
to give it to Andy...

47:47.032 --> 47:52.152
...Violet was like, "I don't need a ring
to prove to the world that you are mine."

47:52.328 --> 47:57.368
All I kept thinking was,
"Jesus, please. Sweet baby Jesus...

47:57.542 --> 48:00.659
...put that ring on Holly's finger
before it winds up on Violet's."

48:01.671 --> 48:04.083
I mean, that was my Gran's ring, JeSS.

48:04.299 --> 48:07.666
It meant a lot that She wanted to
give that to me. Hell, man, I would've loved...

48:07.844 --> 48:10.210
...to have put it on someone one day.

48:10.972 --> 48:13.679
But if that someone had to be Violet....

48:15.685 --> 48:17.141
I don't know.

48:19.564 --> 48:21.805
-Oh, Jason.
-What?

48:21.983 --> 48:25.191
I think you mightjust be
the sweetest man in the world.

48:38.917 --> 48:41.829
[PEOPLE CHATTERING AND
COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

48:43.671 --> 48:46.834
PAM: Of all the horrible things
I've seen in the last 100 years...

48:47.008 --> 48:50.216
-...thiS could be the most disturbing.
ERIC: Yeah.

48:50.386 --> 48:53.674
Oh, come on.
It's fun because we're together.

48:53.848 --> 48:55.349
No, it isn't.

48:55.517 --> 48:58.350
What do Mommy and Daddy
look like again?

49:02.649 --> 49:04.105
Ah.

49:05.860 --> 49:07.145
[LAUGHING]

49:07.320 --> 49:09.060
Someone'S having a good time.

49:09.280 --> 49:13.364
You think Daddy'd be enjoying himself
this much if Sarah got to him first?

49:13.576 --> 49:14.952
ERIC:
I'll get him alone.

49:15.161 --> 49:17.948
You mingle, find the mother.

49:18.123 --> 49:20.910
How? All these bitches look the same.

49:28.925 --> 49:30.506
Mommy?

49:30.677 --> 49:31.917
[GASPS]

49:32.095 --> 49:35.007
-Oh, my God.
-Hi, Mommy.

49:35.181 --> 49:39.094
Sarah, what in he--?

49:41.896 --> 49:42.931
[LOCK CLICKS]

49:43.106 --> 49:45.893
The whole world is looking for you.

49:46.109 --> 49:48.942
What are you doing here?
Have you lost your ever-loving mind?

49:49.112 --> 49:52.149
Oh, my God. I missed you so much.

49:54.993 --> 49:57.450
You look so pretty in that suit.

49:57.620 --> 49:59.736
I forgot how beautiful you were.

50:00.832 --> 50:02.038
What do you want?

50:02.250 --> 50:05.162
And what have you done to your hair?

50:05.336 --> 50:06.746
I'm in trouble.

50:07.755 --> 50:09.336
Well, no Shit, baby girl.

50:09.507 --> 50:12.624
No, I mean real trouble.

50:12.802 --> 50:14.963
And I need help from someone high up.

50:15.138 --> 50:18.551
Someone powerful, right here, right now.

50:19.100 --> 50:20.636
IS Laura Bush out there?

50:22.020 --> 50:23.476
No, she is not.

50:23.688 --> 50:25.849
Well, can you call her?

50:26.024 --> 50:30.188
Sarah, Laura stopped taking my calls
just about the time that that book came out...

50:30.361 --> 50:33.353
...claiming that my daughter
is the monster...

50:33.573 --> 50:37.737
...who created the monsters who are
scaring the Shit out of half the country.

50:37.952 --> 50:39.783
Now, is that true?

50:39.954 --> 50:41.569
Yes.

50:42.290 --> 50:44.827
But I'm not a monster.

50:45.001 --> 50:47.617
I'm a Buddhist.

50:47.795 --> 50:49.501
What?

50:50.340 --> 50:53.082
Look, you have gotta get out of here.

50:53.301 --> 50:56.793
If the liberal media finds out you are
at this event, they are never gonna--

50:56.971 --> 50:59.963
No, Mommy, stop. Listen very closely.

51:00.475 --> 51:02.682
The yakuza are after me.

51:04.896 --> 51:08.013
Oh, darling.

51:09.859 --> 51:11.850
[MOANING AND PANTING]

51:24.707 --> 51:26.698
[MOANING AND PANTING CONTINUE]

51:52.360 --> 51:53.691
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

51:57.699 --> 51:59.360
Paul?

52:04.247 --> 52:07.330
I need to ask you some questions
about your daughter.

52:09.961 --> 52:12.418
Has She come to see you?

52:16.301 --> 52:17.711
[MAN GRUNTS & WOMAN SCREAMS]

52:18.678 --> 52:19.884
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

52:22.598 --> 52:24.054
[GUNSHOTS]

52:27.020 --> 52:28.976
[BOTH SHRIEK]

52:30.356 --> 52:31.436
The yakuza?

52:33.234 --> 52:34.940
Go, move! Get out!

52:36.321 --> 52:37.936
[GUNFIRE]

52:49.292 --> 52:51.453
-Where is your daughter?
-I don't know.

52:54.464 --> 52:55.829
[BOTH PANTING]

52:56.007 --> 52:57.497
Come on!

52:59.761 --> 53:02.093
Come on! Come on!

53:02.889 --> 53:04.299
[NANCY GRUNTING]

53:05.141 --> 53:07.723
-Come on!
-Go on, baby!

53:10.521 --> 53:12.182
[SCREAMING]

53:24.369 --> 53:25.404
[GASPS]

53:27.663 --> 53:29.654
[CHOKING]

53:47.433 --> 53:49.765
[GROANING]

54:01.030 --> 54:03.021
[LOCK CLICKS]

54:37.233 --> 54:39.224
[SNIFFS THEN SIGHS]

55:26.240 --> 55:29.027
What are you doing out here, my love?

55:30.077 --> 55:33.240
Someday soon you'll be buried here too.

55:38.419 --> 55:40.455
I don't want to fight.

55:41.547 --> 55:44.254
But I don't see a way out. Do you?

55:44.467 --> 55:46.003
No.

55:49.472 --> 55:52.714
I have loved you since
the very first time I ever saw you.

55:54.310 --> 55:56.642
Long back as I can remember.

55:56.854 --> 56:02.190
You are my first and only true love.

56:04.570 --> 56:07.812
And you are mine.

56:10.660 --> 56:13.777
I will survive thiS war, Caroline.

56:14.705 --> 56:15.990
And when it's all over...

56:16.999 --> 56:19.081
...I will come back to you...

56:19.669 --> 56:21.830
...and to the children.

56:23.422 --> 56:24.673
I promise you.
